.\" Manpage for bitcoin-descriptor(1) — wallet descriptor emitter.
.TH BITCOIN-DESCRIPTOR 1 "2026-05-23" "bitcoin 1.24.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
bitcoin\-descriptor \- emit a wallet's output script descriptor

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bitcoin descriptor wallet
.I name
.br
.B bitcoin descriptor help

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bitcoin descriptor
is reduced to a single surviving subcommand,
.BR wallet ,
as of 1.24.0. The BIP-380 primitives \(em
.BR checksum ,
.BR verify ,
.B derive
\(em moved to
.BR bitcoin-bip380 (1)
in 1.23.0 (FEAT-035 Stream B) and their deprecated
.B descriptor
aliases were removed in 1.24.0.

The
.B wallet
subcommand stays here (rather than in
.BR bitcoin-bip380 (1))
because it reads
.BR secret (1)-managed
wallet state, which the BIP plugins deliberately don't touch.

.SH OPTIONS
.B bitcoin descriptor
takes no top-level flags.

.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.BI "wallet " name
Emit a checksummed
.BI wpkh( xpub /0/* )
descriptor for the existing wallet
.IR name .
Reads the seed via
.B secret get
.IB name /seed
and derives the
.B m/84h/0h/0h
account xpub via the same pipeline
.B bitcoin wallet derive
uses. The checksum is computed by shelling out to
.BR "bitcoin bip380 checksum" .
.TP
.B help
Print usage. Notes that the
.BR checksum / verify / derive
verbs were removed in 1.24.0.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
A removed subcommand
.RB ( checksum / verify / derive )
was invoked; the error names the canonical
.B bitcoin bip380
form.
.TP
.B \(>=2
Missing argument, no such wallet, or
.B secret
not on PATH. Specific errors emit an
.B error
line to stderr per CLAUDE.md §10.

.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/var/bitcoin/wallets/<name>/
The wallet repository the
.B wallet
subcommand reads from.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B SELF_LIBEXEC
Required: the
.B wallet
subcommand shells out to sibling
.BR bip39 ", " bip32 ", " bip13 ", and " bip380
plugins. Inherited from
.BR bitcoin (1)
when invoked via the dispatcher.

.SH STANDARDS
.IP \(bu 2
BIP-380 (Output Script Descriptors, General Operation) \(em the
descriptor format the emitted string conforms to. The checksum
itself is computed by
.BR bitcoin-bip380 (1).

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bitcoin (1),
.BR bitcoin-bip380 (1),
.BR bitcoin-wallet (1),
.BR secret (1)

.SH HISTORY
Verb introduced in bitcoin 1.0.0 (FEAT-009). The BIP-380
primitives moved to
.BR bitcoin-bip380 (1)
in 1.23.0 (FEAT-035 Stream B); the deprecated
.BR descriptor " " checksum / verify / derive
aliases were removed in 1.24.0, leaving only the
wallet-touching
.B wallet
subcommand.
